FINANCE OFFICE

Associate Accountant (Accounting Operations Section) (Ref. 22011708-E4)

Duties

The appointee will be required to:

(a) perform staff cost analyses and projections for the management and funding bodies;

(b) assist in reviewing and outlining the financial implications on pay level and adjustment reviews for Council’s decision;

(c) assist in enhancement and implementation of systems related to payroll, staff claims and payments;

(d) supervise daily operations of payroll, benefits, staff claims and related payments of the University and its subsidiaries, including verifying payments and related tax filing, and ensuring compliance with the relevant statutory requirements, policies, rules and regulations;

(e) handle general office administration; and

(f) perform any other duties as assigned by the Director of Finance and her delegates.

Qualifications 

Applicants should have:

(a) a recognized degree in Accounting or related disciplines;

(b) a professional accounting qualification or equivalent;

(c) at least three years of post-qualification experience in accounting, auditing or other related fields, preferably with experience in payroll operations, staff benefits, claims processing and/or system enhancement; 

(d) some supervisory experience;

(e) proficiency in Microsoft Office software including Excel, Word and PowerPoint;

(f) a good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese; and

(g) good communication and interpersonal skills.

Shortlisted candidates will be invited to sit for a written test.

Applicants who have responded to the previous advertisement need not re-apply.

Remuneration and Conditions of Service

A highly competitive remuneration package will be offered.  Initial appointment will be on a fixed-term gratuity-bearing contract.  Re-engagement thereafter is subject to mutual agreement.  Applicants should state their current and expected salary in the application.

Application

Please send a completed application form by post to Human Resources Office, 13/F, Li Ka Shing Tower, The Hong Kong Polytechnic University, Hung Hom, Kowloon, Hong Kong or via email by clicking "Apply Now".  Application forms can be downloaded from https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/forms.  If a separate curriculum vitae is to be provided, please still complete the application form which will help speed up the recruitment process. The closing date for application is Monday, 31 January 2022.  Applicants who are not invited to an interview within two months from the closing date should consider their applications unsuccessful. The University’s Personal Information Collection Statement for recruitment can be found at https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/pics_for_recruitment.

PolyU is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversity and inclusivity.  All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to gender, ethnicity, nationality, family status or physical or mental disabilities.

Location: Sheung Wan


Roles & responsibilities:
Conduct risk-based audits and reviews;
draft audit schedules in accordance with pre-defined audit scope and objectives for the superiors’ consideration;
solicit and gather information relevant to audit assignments;
conduct audit tests, including the compliance and substantive tests;
identify audit findings and provide value-added recommendations;
analyze and consolidate audit findings to report to superiors;
assist administrative work of audit team; and
assist in documenting audit findings.
The ideal candidate should possess:

(a) Basic Certificate/Higher Certificate/Diploma in Accounting or Business Administration with 1 year’s accounting/auditing experience; or
(b) Associate Degree/Higher Diploma/Professional Diploma in Accounting or Business Administration;
5 passes in HKCEE including Chinese Language, English Language (Syl.B) and Mathematics or equivalent;
proper technical and communication skills; and
qualities of hardworking and attentive to details.
(Please specify in the resume or application form the relevant academic results/qualifications and working experience you have attained in detail.)


Compensation & employment terms:
The successful candidate will initially be offered a 2-year contract with a remuneration package which will be commensurate with his/her background and experience. The continuation of employment and employment terms thereafter will be subject to mutual agreement. Apart from contributions to the MPF Scheme, other benefits include paid annual leave, medical services, a dental scheme and training sponsorships. The incumbent will normally work under a 5-day week schedule subject to operational needs and exigencies of the service.


Application:

Please send your resume or a completed application form [F601(n)] with indication of your current and expected salaries to the Head of Human Resources Division, Tung Wah Group of Hospitals at 4/F., Wong Fung Ling Memorial Building, 12 Po Yan Street, Hong Kong by 18 January 2022.  Application forms are obtainable in person or can be downloaded from http://www.tungwah.org.hk.  The reference code should be marked both in the letter and on the envelope.  Underpaid mail items will not be accepted by Tung Wah.  For proper delivery of your mail items, please ensure your mail items bear sufficient postage with return address before posting.  Personal data provided by applicants will be used strictly for recruitment purpose only and in accordance with the Tung Wah’s personal data policy.  Applicants not invited to attend an interview by 30 April 2022 may assume that their applications are unsuccessful.
WE ARE AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER

Alfred H.K. Li & Co., CPA is a fast-growing and highly dynamic CPA firm in Hong Kong.

Due to continuous business expansion, we are looking for Audit junior, Semi-senior, Senior auditors and Supervisors who are conscientious, independent, responsible and hardworking.

Requirements:

Diploma/Associate Degree/Degree major in Accounting;
Student member of HKICPA/ACCA or equivalent preferred;
Good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese is essential;
Willing to travel to P.R.C. and fluent in Putonghua;
One to four years’ audit experiences in audit firms preferred;
Good command of knowledge in Microsoft Office and accounting software;
Good interpersonal communication skill;
Able to work under pressure and carry out multi-tasks independently;
Hardworking, honest, responsible and self–motivated; and
Immediate available is preferable.

Remuneration will be commensurate with qualification and experiences.   We offer 5 days’ work, discretionary performance bonus, 12 days annual leave, birthday leave, study and examination leaves and medical allowance.

Interested candidates should forward your resume, expected and present salary and date of availability by clicking Apply Now.

Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only.
